Let's also add a navigation bar and footer to the layout. In the same file, under `<body>` add


= preserve do 
  - code("erb") do
    %nav.navbar.navbar-default.navbar-fixed-top{:role => "navigation"}
      .container
        .navbar-header
          %button.navbar-toggle{"data-target" => ".navbar-collapse", "data-toggle" => "collapse", :type => "button"}
            %span.sr-only Toggle navigation
            %span.icon-bar
            %span.icon-bar
            %span.icon-bar
          %a.navbar-brand{:href => "/"} The Idea app
        .collapse.navbar-collapse
          %ul.nav.navbar-nav
            %li.active
              %a{:href => "/ideas"} Ideas

and before `</body>` add

= preserve do
  - code("erb") do
    %footer
      .container
        Rails Girls 2016

Pay attention to the difference between `<body>` and `</body>`!